## L.6 Status of the Clay scope

The conservative reading of the present results, in light of the
preceding sections, is the following.

> *This paper establishes the $\mathrm{SU}(N)$ Wilson lattice mass gap
> unconditionally (Section 4, Theorems 4--5), and the continuum mass
> gap conditional on the K-uniform spectral lemma question of Tier 1B
> (Section 5). The four Jaffe--Witten structural ingredients catalogued
> in this Appendix L --- renormalised composite operators (L.1),
> short-distance match to perturbative asymptotic freedom (L.2), the
> stress-energy tensor as an operator-valued distribution (L.3), and an
> operator product expansion with prescribed local singularities (L.4)
> --- are stated as open conjectures of comparable difficulty to known
> unsolved problems in 4D non-Abelian constructive QFT. The present
> paper provides a rigorous lattice-to-continuum mass-gap proof modulo
> Tier 1B; the four Clay structural ingredients form a separate
> research programme on top of the mass-gap proof.*

Two pieces of unconditional progress on the structural ingredients are
worth highlighting:

1. *Positivity of the OS Hamiltonian* $H_{\mathrm{OS}} \geq 0$ is
   established directly from OS reconstruction, independently of any
   composite-operator conjecture (L.3.2). This is one of the
   sub-clauses of (iv) of Conjecture L.3.

2. *The coincident-point bound on $S_n$* is established without any
   appeal to the OPE, via Källén--Lehmann + linked cluster
   (§5.7(f)/F1). This closes the OS-axiom verification but does not
   close the structural OPE clause (L.4.5).

The remaining open content of the four conjectures is the genuine
research programme: constructing $[\mathrm{Tr}\,F^2]_R$ on
$\mathcal{H}$, verifying its short-distance asymptotics, identifying
the integrated stress tensor with the OS Hamiltonian, and constructing
a non-perturbative OPE.

A Clay submission cannot honestly claim that any of L.1--L.4 are
established by the main body. The honest position is the conservative
one stated above: a rigorous mass-gap proof (modulo Tier 1B), with the
four structural ingredients of Jaffe--Witten §4 explicitly listed as
open problems.


